com.edugility.liquibase

Class URLResourceAccessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • liquibase.resource.AbstractResourceAccessor
      • com.edugility.liquibase.URLResourceAccessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResourceAccessor

    public class URLResourceAccessor
extends AbstractResourceAccessor
    An AbstractResourceAccessor that delegates most of its work to a delegate ResourceAccessor, while preserving the ability to process Strings that represent URLs.

    Design Notes

    The Liquibase 3.3.0 ResourceAccessor interface is inconsistently documented, and mixes several quite unrelated concerns together. The CompositeResourceAccessor implicitly relies on non-null values being returned from some of its aggregated ResourceAccessors' methods. The combination of these two unfortunate facts means that returning null from methods that do not make sense for a ResourceAccessor like this one that processes URLs is effectively impossible. Consequently, a delegating approach has to be taken instead.

    Author:
    Laird Nelson

    AbstractResourceAccessor, CompositeResourceAccessor, ResourceAccessor

    • Method Detail

      • getResourcesAsStream

        public Set<InputStream> getResourcesAsStream(String path)
                                      throws IOException
        Returns a Set of open InputStreams that the supplied path logically designates.

        This method never returns null.

        This implementation attempts to create a URL from the supplied path, and, if that operation is successful, to return a Set containing only that URL. If a MalformedURLException is encountered during this operation, then the return value of the getResourcesAsStream(String) method invoked on the delegate is returned instead.

        If a null return value is about to be returned for any reason, then the return value of the Collections.emptySet() method is returned instead.

        Parameters:
        path - a String that will be passed unaltered to the constructor of the URL class; must not be null
        Returns:
        a non-null Set of open InputStreams
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if path is null
        IOException - if an input/output error occurs

      • list

        public Set<String> list(String relativeTo,
                        String path,
                        boolean includeFiles,
                        boolean includeDirectories,
                        boolean recursive)
                 throws IOException
        Returns the result of invoking the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time.

        The ResourceAccessor interface does not document any of the parameters to this method. They are passed to the delegate unaltered.

        Parameters:
        relativeTo - a String passed to the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time unaltered
        path - a String passed to the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time
        includeFiles - whether non-directory Files should be returned; passed to the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time
        includeDirectories - whether directories should be returned; passed to the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time
        recursive - if true, a boolean passed to the ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean) method on the ResourceAccessor supplied at construction time
        Returns:
        a Set of Strings, or null
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs
        See Also:
        ResourceAccessor.list(String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean)
